&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time Position Available.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to unforeseen circumstances we are seeking a full time Receptionist.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are currentlylooking to recruitaReceptionist to join our Health Centre/Walk- In Centre in Norwich. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of the busy medical reception team, you will bring an experienced approach to the role, providing the customer focus required for patients and visitors to the Centre and to deal with the day-to-day challenges presented by a diverse population and their needs. The Health Centre is open from 7am – 9pm (Walk-In centre) 8am – 8pm, (Health Centre) We are open 7 days a week, 365 days a year, including weekends and bank holidays. The job holder will cover a mixture of early and late shifts across the opening hours including bank holidays.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ideally you will have previous experience in a healthcare environment and customer service, with an understanding of general practice combined with good administrative skills. Flexibility and an excellent telephone manner are also essential, as is an ability to work under pressure. Previous knowledge and experience of a computerised clinical system (ideally SystmOne) would be desirable. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
